examples.en: The scandal significantly damaged her career.
Health problems can be significantly reduced by careful diet.
The device has lowered the rate of car accidence significantly.
The cost of our raw materials has risen significantly.
If you take my advice, your chances of winning will increase significantly.
Modern machinery has significantly eased the backbreaking work of farming.
People who smoke have a significantly greater risk of developing lung cancer than people who don't.
Another store sold the game for a significantly lower price.
Oil prices fluctuated significantly during October.
Delia's work has been significantly better this year.
The parish has grown significantly in the last three years.
Some people contend that whole wheat bread is significantly more nutritive than white bread.
He looked significantly in her direction when he said that some of us are not doing our jobs.
George paused, and glanced significantly in my direction.
There's no question that that bicycle racer was significantly advantaged by a great set of genes.
Our budget will be significantly affected by these new cuts.
The Democrats, significantly, finished well behind the Green Party.
Crime rates are significantly higher in urban areas (=towns, cities etc).
Methods used by younger teachers differ significantly from those used by older ones.
The value of the coffee becomes significantly higher when expressed in foreign currency.
The slushy racetrack resulted in a significantly slower time for the winning horse.
